            <h2>Sky Airlines Cancellation Policy </h2>
            <p>Sky Airlines is the second-largest flight carrier based in Santiago; Chile founded in 2001. The airline flight operates in Chile and South America and domestic flights within Peru including international routes to Argentina, Brazil, Peru, and Uruguay. </p>
            <p>If you wish to plan a trip, especially for business purposes, make sure you book <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/ ">flight tickets</a> from Sky airlines. Because Sky airlines was declared the most punctual airline in 2016 and in 2022, the airline will merge with Avianca to create a mega low-cost carrier. Let’s understand the uncomplicated cancellation policy of the airlines for a better perspective. </p>
            <h2>Cancellation</h2>
            <p>You can <b>cancel a flight booked on SKY Airlines within 24 hours</b>  of the purchase. The airline will provide a complete refund of your ticket cost in case the booking was made a week or more prior to the departure date of your flight. If you fail to cancel the flight within 24 hours, you will have to pay the cancellation fee as per the fare rule of the airlines somewhere between $100 to $500. </p>
            <p>However, if the airline cancels the flight due to any unavoidable reasons, then it will provide you compensation to book the next subsequent flight. Thus, you can choose to <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/sky-airlines-cancellation-policy.aspx">cancel your flight and get a refund on SKY Airlines</a>.</p>
            <h3>Refund</h3>
            <p>If you have successfully canceled the <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/flight-booking-online-international.aspx">flight reservation</a> within 24 hours of booking, you are eligible to receive a 100% refund. If you have canceled the flight reservation near the flight departure time, the refund would be less as compared to cancellations made within 24 hours. </p>
            <h2>FAQs</h2>
            <h3>How to cancel a flight ticket with Sky airlines?</h3>
            <p>You can call the Sky airlines customer care office and inform them about the cancellation. You may also contact your kiosk to help you through the cancellation process. Apart from this, you may also visit the official website of the airlines and cancel your flight ticket. </p>
            <h3>When can I make the request for the refund? By when can I expect it? </h3>
            <p>You can make a request for a refund by filling out a refund request form on Sky airline’s official website. The refund will reflect in more or less 30 business days, as per your payment method. </p>
            <h3>Can I ask for compensation if my flight gets delayed by 2 hours? </h3>
            <p>If your replacement flight delays your arrival by 2 or more hours or your flight was canceled less than 14 days before departure, you are eligible to get compensation. </p>
            <h3>How to check if my flight is refundable? </h3>
            <p>You can check if your flight is refundable by visiting the official website of the airline and entering the ticket or document number and Sky airline’s website will display refund eligibility and information. </p>
